📊 1. Length of Stay (Where delays are happening)
Orthopedics shows the highest average length of stay (~7+ days)

👉 What this means:

Patients are staying longer than expected

Possible causes:

Slow recovery processes
Delays in discharge planning
Limited post-care support

✅ Business impact:
Fewer beds available
Increased operational cost

🛏️ 2. Bed Usage (Overcrowding Risk)
Bed types (General, ICU, Private) show high and similar usage levels

👉 What this means:
Hospital resources are heavily utilized across all bed types
No clear buffer → risk of overcrowding

✅ Business impact:
Emergency patients may face delays
Staff workload increases

💰 3. Cost vs Severity of Illness
Costs increase with severity (expected)

But moderate and minor cases still show high costs
👉 What this means:

Possible inefficiencies in treatment or billing
Lower severity cases may be over-utilizing resources

✅ Business impact:

Opportunity to reduce unnecessary spending

🚪 4. Discharge Bottlenecks
Patients discharged to:

Home
Rehabilitation
Skilled nursing

👉 All show similar volume
👉 What this means:

No smooth discharge pathway
Possible delays in:

Rehab placement
External care coordination

✅ Business impact:

Beds remain occupied longer

Slows down new admissions

💸 5. Most Expensive Department
Orthopedics = highest total cost

👉 What this means:

Major cost driver in the hospital

Breakdown shows:

Room charges > Medication costs

👉 Interpretation:

Costs are driven more by long stays, not drugs

🔥 Key Problems Identified

1. 🟥 Long Hospital Stays
Especially in Orthopedics

2. 🟥 High Costs Driven by Stay Duration
Not just treatment

3. 🟥 Discharge Delays
Patients not leaving fast enough

4. 🟥 High Bed Utilization
Risk of overcrowding

✅ Strategic Recommendations

✔️ 1. Improve Discharge Planning
Start discharge process earlier

Partner with rehab centers

✔️ 2. Reduce Length of Stay
Introduce:

Fast-track recovery programs

Standard treatment protocols

✔️ 3. Optimize Bed Management
Real-time bed tracking

Prioritize emergency cases

✔️ 4. Control Costs
Focus on:

Reducing unnecessary inpatient days

Shifting minor cases to outpatient care

👉

“Orthopedics is the biggest pressure point—patients stay longer, costs are higher, 
and discharge delays are slowing down hospital flow. 
Fixing discharge efficiency and reducing length of stay will directly improve capacity and reduce cost.”
